HEADWORD: orchestrate
<hw>orchestrate</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to write an
orchestra score for; -- of a musical composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be the chief coordinator of (an activity
requiring action by more than one person); to organize and
coordinate.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mastermind, engineer, direct, organize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>orchestrated</ent>⟦br⟧
